.TH "of_platform_bus_create" 9 "of_platform_bus_create" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_platform_bus_create \- Create a device for a node and its children.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" of_platform_bus_create
.BI "(struct device_node *bus "  ","
.BI "const struct of_device_id *matches "  ","
.BI "const struct of_dev_auxdata *lookup "  ","
.BI "struct device *parent "  ","
.BI "bool strict "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bus" 12
device node of the bus to instantiate
.IP "matches" 12
match table for bus nodes
.IP "lookup" 12
auxdata table for matching id and platform_data with device nodes
.IP "parent" 12
parent for new device, or NULL for top level.
.IP "strict" 12
require compatible property
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Creates a platform_device for the provided device_node, and optionally
recursively create devices for all the child nodes.
